# Business Context

UAP Inc. supports a large network of automotive parts retailers across Canada through enterprise applications, including the Karmak Fusion platform.

The organization operated Karmak Fusion database environments hosted in Microsoft Azure Cloud. As part of a cost optimization and infrastructure strategy initiative, UAP decided to migrate selected enterprise database workloads from Azure Cloud back to on-premises SQL Server infrastructure.

The migration required careful planning to maintain business continuity for retail operations while reducing infrastructure costs.

---

# Business Challenge

The migration presented several technical challenges:

* Large-scale database migration across multiple locations.
* Maintaining application availability during transition.
* Migrating multi-terabyte databases.
* Minimizing downtime for retail operations.
* Ensuring data integrity after migration.
* Establishing disaster recovery capabilities after migration.
* Standardizing SQL Server configurations across environments.

